<L>__{interior chopper}
<A>__{the two men look at each other in silence. they get out. close on a large, makeshift funeral pyre smoldering to a close. a hastily conceived crematorium. wood, books, furniture, tires, anything that will burn has been mixed together with the charred remains of several dogs and the body of a man. curious mounds of a melted and blackened goo are heaped within the mess. a small can of gasoline lies nearby. a large oil drum not far off.}
<B>__{macready and copper}
<A>__{their faces ashen as they take in this grotesque sight. macready turns to view the norwegian compound. he then exchanges a look with copper. macready heads back toward the chopper.}
